						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the compound of the Jaṅgaṁmaṭha.</p>						

						<p>1623 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to register an endowment made by Mummaḍi, Chikkarāya, son of Immaḍi Chikkarāya of Suguṭūru, to his religious preceptor. The details of the grant cannot be made out.</p>						

						<p>It is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Rudhirōdgāri, Jyēshṭha śu. 1[0], [Wednesday].</hi> On palaeographical grounds the record may be assigned to the 17th century, in which case the details of date of the record may probably correspond to 1623 A.D., May 28, Wednesday, f.d.t. ·25.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
